---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
import CTABand from "../components/CTABand.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Our Story · Casa da Nova Vida"
  description="Why Casa da Nova Vida exists: a sanctuary born from the belief that spirituality is the cornerstone of lasting recovery and a truly new life."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Our Story"
    title="Born from a hard-won truth: real healing requires awakening to Spirit"
    intro="Casa da Nova Vida, House of New Life, is a recovery house in the Texas Hill Country founded by Drew Walsh, offering an alternative, holistic path of healing for those working with sacred plant medicine."
    image="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1470252649378-9c29740c9fa8?auto=format&fit=crop&w=2000&q=80"
    imageAlt="Misty hills at first light"
  />

  <section class="px-6 py-20 lg:px-10 lg:py-28">
    <div class="prose-links mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-cocoa">
        Casa da Nova Vida began with our founder, Drew Walsh, and his own long
        journey through addiction and recovery. Across years of using and
        healing, one truth kept surfacing: real healing requires awakening to
        Spirit. So he went all in, facing the wounds that had driven him, and
        discovered that everything he needed was already within, waiting to be
        remembered.
      </p>

      <blockquote
        class="my-14 border-l-4 border-clay pl-6 font-display text-2xl leading-relaxed text-pine"
      >
        “The single most essential attribute of my sobriety became my spiritual
        awareness and my devotion to a life of healing.”
        <cite class="mt-4 block font-sans text-sm not-italic uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-stone">
          Drew Walsh, Founder
        </cite>
      </blockquote>

      <p class="mt-6 leading-relaxed text-cocoa">
        Out of that conviction, Nova Vida was created as a recovery house for
        people walking an alternative path of healing through sacred plant
        medicine. Medicines like Iboga and Ayahuasca can catalyze deep
        breakthroughs, but the healing does not end when the ceremony does. The
        days and weeks that follow are among the most decisive of the entire
        journey, and too often, people are sent home to face them alone. We built
        a home instead: a place to land, stabilize, and weave those insights into
        a lasting new life.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-14 text-2xl text-pine">What we believe</h2>
      <p class="mt-5 leading-relaxed text-cocoa">
        We believe that spirituality is the cornerstone of recovering from
        addiction and building a life of true, balanced well-being. We believe
        healing is holistic: the spiritual, mental, emotional, and physical
        selves cannot be separated, and must be tended together.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 leading-relaxed text-cocoa">
        We believe in humility as the doorway to transformation, the willingness
        to be small, teachable, and honest with ourselves. And we believe in harm
        reduction as a compassionate, realistic approach, one that honors each
        person's path as unique and non-linear, meeting people without judgment
        while gently inviting honesty and self-awareness.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 leading-relaxed text-cocoa">
        And we believe in the quiet power of place, presence, and time. Real
        change is not rushed. It is cultivated, like a garden, in a setting of
        safety, beauty, and belonging.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-14 text-2xl text-pine">The care you'll find here</h2>
      <p class="mt-5 leading-relaxed text-cocoa">
        Our home sits in the Central Texas Hill Country, just outside Austin.
        With only a few guests at a time, the care here is personal, never a
        program you disappear into, but a relationship you're held by. Through
        one-on-one integration coaching, mindfulness and meditation, somatic
        therapies, and holistic lifestyle support, we walk alongside each person
        beyond the ceremony, helping them embody what the medicine revealed and
        build a life of meaning, connection, and freedom.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="pb-20 lg:pb-28"><CTABand
    heading="Come see if this feels like home"
    body="The best way to know whether Casa da Nova Vida is right for you is simply to talk. Reach out. There is no pressure, only a conversation."
  /></div>
</Layout>
